<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,833,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,833,858]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from scattered localities in the Succulent Karoo Biome in the Little Namaqualand region of the Northern Cape Province (
<bibRefCitation author="Bauer" box="[479,624,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Bates, M. F. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2014 a) Afroedura halli (Hewitt, 1935). In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 91 - 92." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Bauer 
<number box="[554,612,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="2014.0">2014</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[647,717,869,894]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1165,1187]" captionTargetBox="[181,1379,205,1164]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[172,1393,177,1165]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map of southern Africa showing the approximate distributional ranges of previously described species of Afroedura. Red dots represent localities sampled for the genetic portion of the study. Ranges based on Branch (1998) and Bates et al. (2014) as well as unpublished data. Taxon names follow the conclusions of this paper. Area demarcated by a dashed line is presented in more detail in Figure 6." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250499/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
Fig. 
<number box="[700,717,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="470" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,833,1182]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,905,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Haacke" box="[321,488,905,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Haacke, W. D. (1965) Additional notes on the Herpetology of South West Africa with descriptions of two new subspecies of geckos. Cimbebasia, 11, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1965">
Haacke (
<number box="[420,480,905,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1965.0">1965</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, in describing 
<taxonomicName box="[651,889,906,930]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="africana" subSpecies="tirasensis">
<emphasis box="[651,889,906,930]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africana tirasensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considered 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1201,906,929]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="namaquensis">
<emphasis box="[1024,1201,906,929]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. namaquensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and it has maintained this rank since (
<bibRefCitation author="Mertens" box="[693,854,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Mertens, R. (1971) Die Herpetofauna Sudwest - Afrikas. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 529, 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1971">
Mertens 
<number box="[795,854,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Branch" box="[868,1015,941,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Branch, W. R. (1981) An annotated checklist of the lizards of the Cape Province, South Africa. Annals of the Cape Provincial Museums (Natural History), 13, 141 - 167." type="journal article" year="1981">Branch 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 1988, 
<number box="[1100,1159,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1998.0">1998</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Onderstall" box="[1172,1356,941,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Onderstall, D. (1984) Descriptions of two new subspecies of Afroedura pondolia (Hewitt) and a discussion of species groups within the genus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). Annals of the Transvaal Museum, 33, 497 - 509." type="journal article" year="1984">
Onderstall 
<number box="[1297,1356,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bauer" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Bates, M. F. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2014 a) Afroedura halli (Hewitt, 1935). In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 91 - 92." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Bauer 
<number box="[151,211,978,1002]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="2014.0">2014</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), although chiefly because this poorly known taxon has not been reviewed subsequently. Under modern species concepts, the differences between the supposed subspecies of 
<emphasis box="[983,1140,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="470">A. africana—</emphasis>
including precloacal pore counts, presence of internasal granules, gular scale counts, and color pattern (
<bibRefCitation author="Haacke" box="[1046,1198,1049,1074]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Haacke, W. D. (1965) Additional notes on the Herpetology of South West Africa with descriptions of two new subspecies of geckos. Cimbebasia, 11, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="1965">
Haacke 
<number box="[1141,1198,1049,1074]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) would generally be accepted as evidence of specific distinctness, especially in light of the large disjunctions between the forms and their likely low vagility (
<bibRefCitation author="Mouton" box="[426,704,1121,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Mouton, P. le F. N. &amp; Mostert, D. P. (1985) Description of a new species of Afroedura (Loveridge) (Reptilia: Gekkonidae) from the south - western Cape. South African Journal of Zoology, 20, 246 - 249." type="journal article" year="1985">
Mouton &amp; Mostert 
<number box="[645,704,1121,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jacobsen" box="[715,883,1121,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" refString="Jacobsen, N. H. G. (1997) Family Gekkonidae, Genus Afroedura. In: Van Wyk, J. H. (Ed.), Proceedings of the FitzSimons Commemorative Symposium, South African Lizards: 50 years of Progress and Third H. A. A. Symposium on African Herpetology, Transvaal Museum, Pretoria, South Africa, 11 - 15 October 1993. Herpetological Association of Africa, Stellenbosch, pp. 34 - 39." type="journal article" year="1997">
Jacobsen 
<number box="[823,883,1122,1146]" pageId="19" pageNumber="470" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). On this basis we here recognize this taxon at the rank of full species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
